Subject: Re: [T2] CAD files in the archive idea

On Thu, Jan 03, 2002 at 10:15:22PM -0500, John Hartranft wrote:
> My concept is to just standardize on the fairly ubiquitous .pdf file for
> uploads to the archive.  Anybody can download them and print them out, they
> can't be changed (makes us designer types sleep better), and it's a
> reasonably efficient file format.

I would suggest creating plot files as well. for things like panel
patterns the user can send the plot file to a plot house w/out any cad
experience and have prints made on large format paper.

